      "snowpackStructure": {
        "comment": "The gusty wind has transported the fresh and old snow significantly. Hard wind slabs formed. These are lying on top of a weakly bonded old snowpack in particular on west, north and east facing slopes above approximately 2200 m. The snowpack will be subject to considerable local variations. In steep terrain there is a danger of falling on the hard snow surface. <br/> <br/> The weather conditions will give rise to moistening of the snowpack. <br/> <br/> In particular on steep sunny slopes at low and intermediate altitudes hardly any snow is lying."
      },
